Vintage / Retro — Project Goals & Experience Blueprint
1) Vision

Deliver a warm, nostalgic, handcrafted experience with modern performance. The interface feels like aged paper and letterpress ink while behaving with crisp, contemporary responsiveness.

2) Aesthetic System (Final Choices)

Palette

#2F2213 Ink

#6B4E2E Sepia-900

#8C6A3B Sepia-700

#B0895E Sepia-500

#E7D9C9 Cream-200

#F6F0E6 Cream-50

Accent Olive #6D8A57, Accent Burgundy #7A3E3E

Typography

Display: Cormorant Garamond (600/700)

Body/UI: Source Serif 4 (400/500/600)

Texture & Finishes

Subtle paper grain overlay (SVG mask at 6% opacity)

Hairline borders (1px, #E2D7C7)

Letterpress shadow (y=1, blur=2, alpha=0.12)

3) Layout & Spacing

Grid: 12-col responsive grid, 72rem max content width.

Spacing Scale: 4, 8, 12, 16, 24, 32, 48, 64.

Radii: 10px cards, 8px buttons, 999px pills.

4) Motion & Micro-interactions

Principle: Motion communicates state, never distracts.

Durations: 160ms micro, 240ms page transitions.

Easing: Cubic-bezier(0.22, 0.55, 0.25, 0.95).

Patterns

Hover: grain intensity +6%, soft raise (translateY(-1px)).

Button press: compress scaleY(0.98) then settle.

Page transition: fade-through sepia wash at 8% opacity over 240ms.

Toggle: flip-card 3D rotateY(8°) with snap back.

Reduced Motion: Respect prefers-reduced-motion (animations disabled; instant state changes).

5) Information Architecture

Home → brand story hero → featured items/services → testimonials → CTA.

Catalog/Services → filter header → card grid → detail pages.

About → timeline with stamps and photos.

Gallery/Lookbook → masonry grid with gentle zoom on reveal.

Contact/Booking → succinct form, success receipt, sepia-styled map.

Journal → short entries with date-stamp badges.

6) Components (Specs)

Header/Nav: Sticky; section underline 2px (#B0895E), active tab emboss.

Card: 10px radius, 1px border #E2D7C7, soft shadow; thumbnail with 5% grain.

Buttons: Primary #8C6A3B on #F6F0E6; text #F6F0E6; focus ring #6B4E2E at 2px outside.

Badges: Ticket-stub silhouette, background #E7D9C9, ink text.

Inputs: Background #F6F0E6, border #E2D7C7, focus ring #6D8A57.

Pagination: Numbered tabs styled as film perforations with 1px inner shadow.

7) Content & Tone

Voice: Warm, succinct, confident.

Microcopy: Verb-first (“View menu”, “Book a chair”, “See the set”).

Alt Text: Context-rich (“hand-stitched leather wallet on wooden counter”).

8) Accessibility

Body contrast ≥ 4.5:1, large text ≥ 3:1.

Focus states visually distinct from hover.

Keyboard navigation complete; semantic landmarks in templates.

9) Quality & Performance

Targets: LCP < 2.5s, CLS < 0.1, TTI < 2.5s.

Image formats AVIF/WEBP with width-based srcset.

Grain/texture via non-blocking SVG masks; lazy-load non-critical media.

